text: God I hate this blonde douche from Logan as the lead. Overacting, pretentiously superficial idiot. I hope both the classic and super predator make you realize how very little your character is lols. All the same, the other leads, my crush, deadly gorgeous and talented Olivia Munn, and of course the emo, yet  badass Thomas Jane are in it as leads as well. Further, the special effects and costume designs look just as good as avp and better than predators (3rd film.) Surprisingly, several plots are underway in it as well unlike most other predator films. A crashed yautja ship with commandos going after it as a flashback, a scientist and the government knowledgeable of the yautja and even on to their motives going to earth, and one even being autopsied, finally exploring the predators biology; what looks to be an interesting felon story in Thomas Jane, and of course, these tall, dark super predators whose origin is unknown. I've also had my eye on Shane Black a while and his direction and storytelling gets better with each of his films for me.  He was also one of the original lead cast and probably has a lot of soul from the original in him. Very interesting and exciting. My body is ready, my returned childhood terror.

Sure, Shane Black will bring something special to the writing for character dynamics and banter, but it's too bad he learned nothing from John McTiernan's visual aesthetic when acting in McTiernan's original classic. I just see no artistry here. Should have begged John to return to direct.

text: Shane Black is a genius. Throughout all of recorded history, the concept and/or embodiment of what a true "Predator" is... equates to an ever-changing organism with the passage of time. Apex predators evolve and adapt, staying at the top of their respective food chain/s as a result.  There are some absolutely frightening species of animals, insects, and even foliage out there when you really ponder this concept for a moment.   What Shane Black has done...   ...is cleverly apply the concept of predators always remaining innately superior to their prey over time, via not only science and technological advantages, but also through sheer evolution (as a result of their combined prowess with the former).    This will truly be an exciting new page in the Predator film verse. The trailer looks good; now all that's left to do is hope the final cut is an action packed, no frills blockbuster... and one that's structurally well made. I'm very excited for this film and will definitely see it.

text: It feels like this trailer gives the whole movie away and it doesn't look original. If they are going for a "the enemy of my enemy is my friend" thing, it was done in AvP. If they are going for a "mutated predator that's the ultimate threat" it was done in AvP Requiem. If they are going for a "two classes of predators that are rivals" it was done in Predators (2010). And if they're going for all of them in one film...that doesn't make it good.   I feel like they missed a great opportunity here to expand the mythos of the universe. Instead of the "monster" being a predator on steroids, I feel a better angle would be a whole new alien species; for example, they say they have conquered the galaxy so what if the monster ends up being a member of one of the first species they thought they exterminated a millennia ago but have actually been recovering and growing in some back corner solar system.   OR  I think it would be bad ass if they used the original design of the predator from the very first film (the one that's all red with the long neck). They'd obviously have to tweak it's design to make it less corny looking but I think it would be a great call back for fans.

text: I see a load of typical cockbag idiots that comment negative on the movie. All Iâ€™ve heard and seen on YouTube and the net during the build up of this movie is negative vibes, either rumours about the plot being bad, the cast being bad, if the predator will side with the humans or not... now the second trailer is out people saying â€œoh thanks for showing the mutant predator now I donâ€™t have to watch itâ€ amongst other things. This movie doesnâ€™t stand a chance because of so many twats online that just have to be negative about everything. The first predator movie was a one off in the sense that it was so fresh at the time! Iâ€™m 38 now and I remember watching that for the first time as a kid and being totally in awe at it! After I watched it and it scared the shit outa me lol, I woke and ran downstairs the next morning to watch it again on vhs and pausing it to see if I could see the predator when cloaked ðŸ˜‚, itâ€™s was just amazing and of course Arnie. But then the second one came out and people bitched... oh itâ€™s no way as good as the 1st, or when the cross over with the aliens came out you had the fucking geeky melts bitching and whinging about how itâ€™s not following the comics religiously and the movies are a joke! For fuck sake...  the movie predators I thought was awesome but people still slagged it off and said it was a joke. Now with this movie the bollocks has started again. Any movie with the predator in it is great, his or their presence on screen, that cackle, the cloaking device, his array of weapons.... just the sheer brutality of his killing is just brilliant. None of the movies stories have sucked, none of them have made you want to fall asleep or walk out, and you are left with a smile on your face after a bit of escapism. text: I don't think this trailer was too long at all.   For one, this does not look like a Reboot but for whatever reason the title they used makes it seem like one.  They had to show enough to let you know it wasn't a reboot.   Also... I have seen trailers that spoil movies and give it away.  I don't think this was one.  I just hope the movie's long.  For those interested in story and plot this was a good trailer.  They introduced a lot of interesting material that couldn't be effectively introduced without a decent length.  If they expound on all that well in the movie it's gonna be bad ass.  If they rush through all those elements like they often do it will suck.

text: Well now I don't have to see the movie because this showed me everything I need to know .  Also thanks for the warning for profanity . Good thing my kid wasn't watching this with me . The original didn't have to have profanity every two seconds like so many movies do these days . I mean is it really necessary ? It won't help with the plotline or anything else but hey it makes people sound ""tough"" -- right ?  The first two are still the best ,but that's just my own opinion . Sorry but I'm just getting sick of reboots that end up failing and sequels several years after the fact . Terminator is a good example of this . It should have been 1-2-3 done but it got dropped ,then picked up by different people with ambitious plans and then dropped again for years and then again picked up with more planned and now dropped again probably for good unless James Cameron acts on his promises to do another one.  For years fans have wanted to see how the story ends with the all out final battle between machine and man but we only get glimpses and then more present day scenarios and once again a planned reboot .   How about doing something creative and original for a change and if they're going to make a series of movies ,finish the damn things and move on ?  Case in point Avatar . How long have fans been waiting for a sequel ? Oh thats right 9 years !! I hear they're done with most of the filming for the next few but we'll still have to wait for another 2 years because of post production and editing . Sorry but none of these actors are getting any younger and you lose momentum when you wait so long in-between films .   I can see waiting for a couple of years between films like with Star wars but a decade or more ?? That's just ridiculous .   Well at least in the meantime we have Marvel movies to keep the pace and keep entertaining the audiences if that's your cup of tea .

text: Watch the making of the Predator movie and appreciate the sheer scale of the film and where they had to film.  The actors for the most part were quite hard guys, they were put through gruelling training and there was real tension and competition - a lot of big guys trying to out do each other in the gym.  The cinematography is excellent, a classical soundtrack and it's shot on film - heavy 35mm rigs, gear and tracks had to be hauled through dense jungle - even the crew were tough!.  They had to reshoot a tonne of stuff, which allowed a rare chance to review the first draft and improve it with a second shoot - they even remade the Predator character, because the first one looked ridiculous.  If Jean Claude Van Dam hadn't walked off set playing the original Predator it may never have become what it did.  Shane Black was there for all of it and one can only hope that he at least knows what magic and luck it took to produce the original.

People say stuff like "They are too basic and make the Predator go by the same old story line" OK, that's fine but how the fuck else is the Predator going to get to earth? Why would it come to earth? And most damning of all...     -The predators motivations has changed from hunting humans for sport... To hunting humans for their DNA to improve their own DNA. text: Damn what's with all the constipated artsy fartsy bullshit complaints and whining here??? Just from seeing a trailer everyone  Suddenly becomes Siskel and Ebert? Pro movie critics? It's a damn Sci Fi Movie. It also looks to be  full of action. Why compare one movie to the next. Arnold had his time and now it's a different era. The predator story is supposed to evolve. These creatures aren't just relegated to jungles. It was inevitable given the story arc that they would branch out and wreak havoc on other segments of society. It was also Inevitable that man would eventually obtain at least one of them in order to understand the science and dynamics behind them.  The funny thing is most of the guys whining on here like someone stole their cereal box, will probably be out there amongst the FIRST to go see it. Get a grip.

text: Dear people who hold the rights to the Predator. #predator2018  This is the second time you had extra big predators fighting regular predators.  Consider.  The Predator as a creator goes after the toughest thing it can find. In many comics it tries to match its skills with the prey. Consider how many ways there are to hunt humans.  WE HAVE SEEN jungle hunting for humans. We have seen urban hunting for humans. We have seen ceremonial right of passage hunting in Alien Vs Predator.  Here are some thoughts. 1) A predator ship shoots off an EMP on earth near a maximum security prison. A team of predators show up, their leader disarms all his high tech gadgets, the other predators guard the exits, and their leader indulges in killing the toughest serial killers mankind has to offer in a closed  space by the dozens HAND TO HAND. Protagonist:wrongfully imprisoned 20 year old and a 50 year old inmate who got arrested for weed use before it was legal and is just stuck in red tape. They are dodging the mayhem of the prison riot and the Predator thrill seeker. PREDATOR: ARENA  2) A predator comes to earth alone. He is not in jungle gear, but a sleekarmor that seems to hold a more slender frame. We see this predator go invisible, kill people, steal their identities (in the online sense and their security information), and slowly  take apart a small country through dismantling power plants, leaking sensitive information, and assassinating powerful politicians with heavy security. His only motivation is to see  how far he can slaughter people back into the stone age. Protagonist: a government agent (Like say the Serbian FBI) and a college kid terrorist he recently captured under the assumption his organization was responsible for these "terrorist attacks". They see their small country fall apart with no one benefitting only to realize this alien monster was only testing his limits. PREDATOR: FOREST FIRE.  3) I am stealing from a Batman crossover book on this: A family of predators are training one of their juveniles to hunt. The go to a southern town in the US, cut it off , slash the tires of all the trucks, and steal human children to act as bait so the juvenile predator can shoot fish in a barrel carving up red necks and veterans. PREDATOR: FIRST HUNT.  4) Have you ever ready up on Ghengis Kahn? He turned a nation of hunters into the world's strongest army. You know what he did at the end of his reign? Took all his warriors, cut off an area the size of a country, and let everyone hunt to their heart's content for 7 days straight everything they can shoot or stab. Have a predator General come down with a whole army, EMP the earth, select a 400 mile wide territory filled with heavily armed humans, and just have them go to town like red necks shooting rabbits. PREDATOR: VICTORY CRY

The predator had just enough screen time to get your pop corns spilling. Most of the crew never saw it coming. text: Trust me the new Predator movie is one of the greatest achievements in human history. If you can't afford a ticket you should sell an organ to go see this so you can say you were there. This movie will definitely have a massive effect on how you live your life. It used a revolutionary writing system of taking ten writers giving them ten index cards each, and told them to write ten things, unconnected things that would look or sound cool and put all 100 of them into a box, shook the box and pulled 10 of them out at random and used them as the main points of the script. They took those and convinced someone to give them millions of dollars to bring this to theaters. That has to be one of the single greatest achievements in human history. If you are a die hard fan of the original film, books, comics, and the lore this movie will let you experience what it feels like to have your spine ripped from your body by a predator. The military technical advisors for this film did a fantastic job that would leave even the most accomplished Stolen Valor guy wanting.

text: I seriously don't understand why do predator movies suck so bad. Comparing to the latest Alien movies,  Prometheus (2012) and Alien: Covenant (2017) the plot for the films were good , it provides us insight on the different races, the engineers, the alien hybrids and the androids, having a background story on the different characters helps ALOT.  The Predator film did not even have any back ground story on the predator, the plot is too fast paced and filled with unnecessary corny ass jokes. The actors in the movie have so much potential with stars like Olivia Munn and Alfie Allen. Like what the actual fuck, the scientific organization is being lead by an ass head that wants to know if this extraterrestrial being actually had intercourse with a human due to its DNA having high resemblance to a human's. At least show us how the predator hunt, their hunting methods their technology advancement compared to the humans. This is really a disappointment, 3/10.
